      "category": "ai",
      "title": "Claude Fable produced a counterexample to the Jacobian Conjecture",
      "url": "https://xcancel.com/__alpoge__/status/2079028340955197566",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48973869",
      "score": 379,
      "comments": 219,
      "author": "loubbrad",
      "published": "2026-07-20T02:51:16Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Anthropic's Claude model generated a purported counterexample to the Jacobian Conjecture, a famously unsolved algebraic geometry problem.",
        "Complex mathematical claims by LLMs often contain subtle algebraic errors, underscoring persistent limitations in deep symbolic reasoning and verification.",
        "Validating LLM-generated math requires integrating neural models with automated theorem provers like Lean to eliminate hallucinations and verify proofs."
      ]
    },
